.TH DELPHI-COLOUR 1  "delphitools-cli 0.1.0" "delphitools manual"
.SH NAME
colour \- Convert a colour between formats
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcolour\fR [\fB\-p\fR|\fB\-\-pretty\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fICOLOUR\fR> [\fIFORMATS\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Convert a colour between formats
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-pretty\fR
Show a pretty colour card
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fICOLOUR\fR>
Colour to convert (hex, rgb, hsl, oklch, oklab, or name)
.TP
[\fIFORMATS\fR]
Target formats (hex, rgb, hsl, oklch, oklab, lab). Shows all if omitted
